<p>I have the following launchd configuration (stored in <code>acme.plist</code>) which I load and start using <code>launchctl load acme.plist</code> and <code>launchctl start acme.plist</code> respectively. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd"&gt; &lt;plist version="1.0"&gt; &lt;dict&gt;     &lt;key&gt;Label&lt;/key&gt;     &lt;string&gt;com.acme&lt;/string&gt;      &lt;key&gt;ProgramArguments&lt;/key&gt;     &lt;array&gt;         &lt;string&gt;/usr/bin/java&lt;/string&gt;         &lt;string&gt;-jar /usr/local/acme/acme-latest.jar&lt;/string&gt;     &lt;/array&gt;      &lt;key&gt;StandardErrorPath&lt;/key&gt;     &lt;string&gt;/tmp/acme-error&lt;/string&gt; &lt;/dict&gt; &lt;/plist&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Whenever I try to run it, I get the following in <code>/tmp/acme-error</code>:</p>  <pre><code>Unrecognized option: -jar /usr/local/acme/acme-latest.jar Error: Could not create the Java Virtual Machine. Error: A fatal exception has occurred. Program will exit. </code></pre>  <p>Yet I have absolutely no problems when running from bash. Any ideas?</p>